<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from Oil and Gas UK (HCS0007)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from Oil and Gas UK (HCS0007)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:21.28pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Executive Summary</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 4pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Oil &amp; Gas UK is the trade association that speaks for the whole sector and is the definitive source of information about the UK upstream. It serves as the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">gateway to industry networks and expertise.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 4pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Offshore helicopter operations are routinely conducted in a hostile marine environment, hence the need to ensure that high levels of flight safety are pre-requisite.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 4pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">No other country in which the oil and gas indu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">stry operates puts more effort into improving its aviation safety performance through leadership, communication and co-operation.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 4pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The UK industry recognises the importance of joined-up working and engages the workforce and trade unions in offshore helicopt</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">er safety awareness through offshore safety committees and onshore networks.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 4pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">1.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Since 1992, six fatal accidents have claimed the lives of 47 offshore workers and flight crew and there have been 18 non-fatal accidents.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 4pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">1.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">However, to determine how safe offshore h</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">elicopter flights are requires an understanding of all facets of offshore helicopter flight operations and rotorcraft engineering.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 4pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">1.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Comparisons between the safety performances of countries should be considered in relation to the measure of success in strivi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ng to meet the primary objective of ensuring that everything that can reasonably be done to minimise the risks is being done.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 4pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">1.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Many safety initiatives have been funded and implemented by the oil and gas industry over the past 35 years.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 4pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">1.9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This includes project</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s jointly funded by oil and gas companies with the regulators (CAA and Health &amp; Safety Executive), helicopter operators and other involved organisations (e.g. National Air Traffic Service (NATS), aircraft and equipment manufacturers).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 4pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">1.10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Helicopter Task G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">roup (HTG) and Helicopter Safety Steering Group (HSSG) are the other oil and gas industry groups dealing with helicopter operations but they serve different purposes. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 4pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">1.11</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Since the early days in the North Sea there has been almost constant regulatory evolutio</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n. The current legislative basis for UK aviation flight operations and airworthiness are well established, of a high level, and kept under constant scrutiny by CAA.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 4pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">1.12</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">As the regulatory spread of EASA continues to grow and increase its influence over UK </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">aviation operations and airworthiness, etc. the UK Government should ensure that CAA resources and regulatory focus is properly maintained in order to reinforce CAA’s ability to continue applying high standards in UK aviation safety.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 4pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">1.13</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">HSE regulate and has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the oversight for helicopter activities on offshore installations. They do this in conjunction with CAA via a Memorandum of Understanding. HSE’s offshore inspectors effectively provide oversight of safety improvements to do with helideck operations</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:14.18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Oil </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&amp; Gas UK</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Oil &amp; Gas UK is the leading representative body for the UK offshore oil and gas industry. It is a not-for-profit organisation, established in April 2007 but with a pedigree stretching back over 40 years.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Membership is open to all companies active</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in the UK continental shelf</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (UKCS)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, from super majors to large contractor businesses and from independent oil companies to SMEs working in the supply chain.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Its predecessor was the UK Offshore Operators Association</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (UKOOA)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our aim is to strengthen the l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ong-term health of the offshore oil and gas industry in the United Kingdom by working closely with companies across the sector, governments and all other stakeholders to address the issues that affect our business.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Health and safety is an important part o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">f any industry, particularly in the offshore </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">oil and gas </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">sector, which is classe</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">d as a major hazards industry.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ffshore helicopter operations are routinely conducted in a hostile </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">marine </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">environment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">hence the need to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> ensure that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">high levels of flight </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">safety are pre-requisite.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UK offshore oil and gas </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">industry</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">committed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to continually improving</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> safety standards for all aspects of offshore helicopter operations</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Few other countries in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> which the oil and gas industry operates </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">puts more effort into improving its </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">aviation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">safety performance through leadership, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">communication and co-operation than the UK.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Transparent reporting of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UK offshore aviation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">safety performance</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and learning from accidents and incidents</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> is achieved thro</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ugh information sharing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">with International</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and European </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">industry </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">aviation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">safety forums. The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UK </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">industry recognises the importance of joined-up working and engages the workforce and trade unions </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in offshore helicopter safety awareness </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">through offshore safe</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ty committees and onshore networks.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The industry operates </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">generally </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">within a goal setting </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">safety </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">regulatory framework </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">but also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">adheres to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the prescriptive </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">aviation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">requirements that apply to offshore helicopter operations. T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">hrough </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the publication of robus</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">t aviation management guidelines, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">information dissemination, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">workshops and seminars, developing and delivering industry-w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ide initiatives and programmes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and engaging with governments and other external organisations, the UKCS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">widely regarded as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a global </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">exemplar of good </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">aviation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">safety practice.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:14.18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">How safe are offshore helicopter flights?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Reference </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to Section 4 in the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">il &amp; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Health &amp; Safety Report 2013 will provide details </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">about</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the UKCS </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Offshore Helicopter Transport Safety Record</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> up to the end of 2012</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> The report can be accessed at:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><a href="http://www.oilandgasuk.co.uk/Health_Safety_Report_2013.cfm"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.oilandgasuk.co.uk/Health_Safety_Report_2013.cfm</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In addition</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> under Supporting Documents</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">this web page includes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Appendix 2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">provides a complete listing of the 72 reportable accidents involving helicopters serving the UK offshore oil and gas sector from 1976 to 2012.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="color:#ff7121; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Since 1976, commercial air transport helicopter flight sta</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tistics and reportable accident </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">data</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for UKCS offshore operations ha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> been collected by the industry along with relevant reports obtained from the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Civil Aviation Authority (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">CAA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Mandatory Occurrence Repo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rting (MOR) scheme. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">During this </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">37-year period up to year-end 2012, more than 6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> million passengers ha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ve been transported to and from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">offshore installations on the UKCS, with over 7.5 million flights made (secto</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rs flown), consuming </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">over</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> 3.5 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">million flying hours. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Regrettably, during this period, 12 fatal accidents have cl</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">aimed the li</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ves of 115 offshore </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">workers and flight crew. There have been 60 non-fatal accidents.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Health &amp; Safety Report 2013 provides a report that is representative of today’s offshore flight ope</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rations using a fleet of modern </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">helicopters. Data from 1992 to 2012</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> have been used for comparative purposes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">measure of current UKCS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> activity, in 2012, just over 1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,000 sectors were</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> flown, consuming 86,000 flight </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">hours and transporting </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">just short of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> a million passengers offshore. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Since 1992, six f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">atal accidents ha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ve claimed the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">lives of 47 offshore workers and flight crew and there have been 18 non-fatal accidents.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">U</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">se of this statistical</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ly</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">small </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">data </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">set </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">does not determine “how safe are offshore helicopter flights”. To reach a sensible conclusion this requires a much deeper understanding of all facets of offshore helicopter </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">flight </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">operations</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rotor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">craft engineering</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Most important when assessing aircra</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ft technical failures is to recognise that for helicopter types used globally in the same role, a major component failure resulting in a crash or ditching (as identified by the AAIB in their reports into the Eurocopter AS332L2 [G-REDL] fatal accident in 20</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">09 and two Eurocopter EC225 accidents [G-REDW and G-CHCN] in 2012), could have occurred anywhere in the world; regardless of where the helicopter was being flown, over land or sea.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Indeed, when offshore helicopter accident rates on the UKCS are compared w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ith the International Oil &amp; Gas Producers Association (OGP) Aviation Safety Committee’s (ASC) worldwide fatal and non-fatal reportable accident rates for the period 1995 to 2010 the data indicates that, averaged over this time, offshore helicopter operatio</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ns on the UKCS carry significantly less risk than operations elsewhere in the world.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:28.35pt"><tr><td style="background-color:#d9d9d9; border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border