t-size:11pt">The AS332L2 non-fatal ditching accident whilst on the approach to BP ETAP </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">February </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2009 [G-REDU]</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> was attributed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> by AAIB</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> largely</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">flight crew perceptual and procedural issues in the final approach</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. There was no loss </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of life and the 18 people involved were all rescued.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.15</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In the absence of completed investigations and a report by AAIB, it </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">inappropriate for O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">il &amp; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UK to comment </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in detail </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">or speculate </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">about outcomes from the AS332L2 [G-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">WN</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">SB</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">]</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> fatal accident off Sumburgh o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">23 August </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2013.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.16</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">However, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">AAIB published a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Special Bulletin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2013</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">on 18 October 2013 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> state</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">no evidence of a technical fault </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">with G-WNSB </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">has been found that could have been causal to the accident</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">”</s