="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">on the UKCS, helicopter operations are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">conducted in a hostile marine environment </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">exclusively </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">wo-engine, two-pilot operations.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> W</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">hereas, for example,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in the US Gulf Coast region there are a large number of small, single-engine helicopter and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">single-pilot operations</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> conducted in relatively benign marine </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">environments and a variety of onshore </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">environments</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">When attempting to make </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">aviation safety </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">comparisons with other North Sea states it should be noted that the UK has the largest helicopter fleet size and significantly higher rates of utilisation and passengers carried</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (e.g. twice the flight hours flown in Norway)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Further</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">other North Sea </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">helicopter </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">operations are principally conducted by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">subsidiaries of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the same </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">helicopter </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">companies that provide the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">bulk of helicopter services on the UKCS; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">generally </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">working to the same aviation rules</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e.g. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">JAR-Ops 3)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">operating</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">maintenance</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">flight </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">safety </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">requirements / </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">guidelines</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> pilot and engineer training regimes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, etc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Ultimately, comparisons between the safety performances of countries </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">should</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">considered in relation to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> measure </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">success in striving to meet </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the prim</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ary</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">objective of ensuring that everything that can </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">reasonably </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">be done </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to minimise the risks </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is being done. As outlined elsewhere in this submission, we believe that the UK has been and remains a global leader in helicopter safety.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:14.18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">What steps could be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">taken by industry to improve the safety of offshore flights?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It is not unreasonable to say that having invested very heavily in replacing an ageing fleet of helicopters on the UKCS with the very latest technology rotorcraft available in the global marketplace, UK helicopter operators and the oil and gas companies al</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ike are shocked </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">dismayed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">by the severity and outcomes of the accidents, in the past </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">four </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">years.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Appendix 3 of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the Oil &amp; Gas UK Health &amp; Safety Report 2013</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">referred</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">paragraph 3.1 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">provides a full and detailed list of industry-led safety </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">initiatives and CAA research projects</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Appendix can be accessed at:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><a href="http://www.oilandgasuk.co.uk/Health_Safety_Report_2013.cfm"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.oilandgasuk.co.uk/Health_Safety_Report_2013.cfm</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">il &amp; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UK A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">viation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">afety </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">echnical </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">roup (AS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">TG)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">its </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">predecessor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> UKOOA Aircraft Committee</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">have</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> a long history of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">taking the init</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ative </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and aggressively driving forward projects </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to improve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> offshore helicopter safety.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Having identified</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> routine and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">sometimes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">unusual operational and technical issues and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">discovered </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">problems that require</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> resolution</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> along with learning from the hard lessons arising from fatal and non-fatal accidents and incidents</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">many safety initiatives have been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">funded and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">implemented </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">by the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">oi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">l and gas </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">industry over the past 35 years. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This includes a long list of research projects which are often jointly funded </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">by oil and gas companies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">with the regulators (CAA and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Health &amp; Safety Executive</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">), helicopter operators and other involved organisations (e.g. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">National Air Traffic Service (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">NATS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">aircraft and equipment manufacturers).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UKOOA Aircraft Committee was initially formed by a group comprised of aviation specialists from oil and gas </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">companies and in the mid-1990s this group was opened up to include senior representatives from the regulators</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, agencies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and helicopter operators. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This composition </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">remains</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> today in the O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">il &amp; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UK ASTG.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Hard won experience of working </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">together </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">jointly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">solve problems and implement new ways of doing business </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in a challenging and hostile </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">marine </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">environment </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">continues today and is the foundation for continuous improvement.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">H</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">elicopter </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ask </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">roup</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(HTG) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and H</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">elicopter </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">afety </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">teering </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">roup</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(HSSG) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the other </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">oil and gas industry</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> groups </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">dealing with helicopter operations but they serve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> different purposes. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">HTG was initially formed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">as the body tasked to focus on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">oil and gas </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">industry responses</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to the 2009 fatal </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">helicopter </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">accident. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">HTG was formed as a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">multi-agency working group comprising </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">executive and senior </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">representatives</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> from O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">il &amp; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UK, oil and gas companies, the offshore contractors, the helicopter operators, CAA, HSE, Maritime &amp; Coastguard Agency, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Grampian Police, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Trades Unions (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">RMT, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Unite</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and BALPA) and the offshore workforce.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">HTG had full executive authority to maintain collective overview by all the stakeholders of the accident investigation outcomes and respond promptly to Air Accident Investigation Board (AAIB) findings and recommenda</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tions; along with reviewing all the activities to do with providing accident victims family support, management of the emergency response, robustness of aviation management guidelines and workforce communications, etc.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.11</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">To work </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">quickly and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">effectively when</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> problems </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">had been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">identified and solutions </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">were </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">being sought, HTG had full authority to initiate research and other studies to improve </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">offshore </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">helicopter safety. It did this in several areas such as pressing the aircraft manufacture</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s to develop </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(from a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">research project) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and implement Advanced Anomaly Detection</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (as production AAD systems)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to enhance </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the performance of Health and Usage Monitoring Systems (HUMS) for improved fault detection in the major dynamic components (e.g. main rotor gearboxes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and tran</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">smission</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">).</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Furthermore, s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ince 2012, all workers flying offshore have been provided with personal locator beacons, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tested to a CAA standard.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.12</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Subsequently,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> after the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">HTG’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> role </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of oversight of the 2009 accident came to a logical end it was decided to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">contin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ue </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the valuable work that had been done to improve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> workforce communication and engagement on helicopter </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">passenger </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">safety under a new group, the HSSG</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, within the industry </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">lead </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">safety body, Step Change in Safety</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.13</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">F</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ollowing the 2012 / 13 accidents </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">HSSG </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">immediately </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">undertook a similar role to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">HTG to provide </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">collective </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">industry responses</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and provide the conduit for workforce communications and engagement</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.14</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">However, HSSG</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> membership</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> has become unwieldy in recent times so, HTG has been re-established as a sm</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">all </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">executive management oversight group and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">HSSG</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> reverted to its previous role.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.15</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ASTG continues to focus on resolving </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a wide range of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">technical </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and operational </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">issues</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">progressing solutions and further developing and refining Aviation Management Guidelines in conjunction with all the stakeholders. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:14.18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">How could legislation and regulations relating to helicopter safety be improved?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">6.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There is already an abundance of legisla</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tion and regulations relating to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> offshore helicopter operations.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; text-decoration:none">6.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Since the early days in the North Sea there has been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">almost </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">constant regulatory evolution. The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">current </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">legislative basis for UK aviation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">flight </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">operations and airworthiness </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are well </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">established, of a high level</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">kept </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">under constant scrutiny by CAA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:14.18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">How effective are existing regulators, including the European Aviation Safety Agency, in ensuring that recommendations to improve safety are implemented?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">As the regulatory spread of E</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ASA continues to grow and increase its influence over UK aviation operations and airworthiness, etc. the UK Government should ensure that CAA resources and regulatory focus is properly maintained in order to reinforce CAA’s ability to continue applying hig</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">h standards in UK aviation safety.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> key </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to future offshore helicopter safety improvements </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is for the UK to retain th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">well-established</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> high level of flight operations</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> requirements, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">airworthiness re</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">quirements and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">regulatory scrutiny by CAA;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> regardless of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Directives issued </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">European Aviation Safety Agency (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">EASA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">EASA </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is seeking a baseline regulatory standard to satisfy all European states and in so doing is in danger of diluting the ‘gold standard’ that has been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">an overriding objectiv</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in the UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, since the early days of aviation.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">CAA is at the forefront of ensuring that UK aviation activities conducted by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the offshore helicopter </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Air Operators Certificate (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">AOC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Holders working in the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">remains</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> safe.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Likewise</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for oversight of airworthiness and air traffic services.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">HSE regulate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and has the oversight </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> helicopter activities on offshore installations. They do this in conjunction with CAA via a Memorandum of Understanding</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> HSE’s offshore inspectors effectivel</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">y provide oversight of safety improvements to do with helideck operations.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It is not immediately apparent that EASA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">respond</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> vigorously or in a timely manner to the many recommendations that have made in AAIB reports into recent offshore accidents. For instance, there is little evidence of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">EASA </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">progress with the 13 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of 27</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> safety recommendations </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">put forward</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">report of the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">AS332L2 non-fatal ditching accident in 2009 [G-REDU].</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_GoBack"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>